      "span_text": "where for brevity we have denoted and where L Each of the energy levels (2.19) associated with a given value of n is seen to be fourfold degenerate (twice with respect to the sign of κ and, after the latter is fixed, twice with respect to the sign of m κ ), except for the one for which κ = −(n − 1 2 ); the latter is only doubly degenerate (with respect to the sign of m κ )."
